<h2>For what purpose do we process your personal data?</h2>
<p>We process your data for the following purposes:</p>
<ol>
    <li>
        <strong>Managing the membership application.</strong> Through the public form we collect
        only your first name, surname(s), email address, telephone number, and the amount and
        frequency with which you wish to collaborate. This data is used to generate an application
        that the Association's staff review before formalising the membership. At this initial
        stage <strong>neither the IBAN nor any bank details are requested</strong>.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Managing the membership relationship.</strong> If the application is approved, we
        formalise the membership. At that point, and now outside the public form, the IBAN is
        collected and the SEPA direct debit mandate required to manage the collection of the fee
        is established. We process this data to administer the membership relationship, respond to
        your communications and comply with our legal, accounting and tax obligations.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Collection of the fee by direct debit.</strong> On the basis of the SEPA mandate,
        we manage the periodic charging of the fee through the bank.
    </li>
</ol>
<p><strong>No automated decisions are taken and no profiling is carried out</strong> with your data.</p>

<h2>What is the legal basis for processing your data?</h2>
<p>The legal basis for the processing is:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>The performance of a contract</strong> to which you are a party, understood as the membership relationship and the steps taken prior to your application (Art. 6.1.b GDPR). This covers both the handling of the membership application and the management of member status and the collection of the direct-debited fee.</li>
    <li><strong>Compliance with legal obligations</strong> applicable to the Association, in particular accounting and tax obligations (Art. 6.1.c GDPR).</li>
</ul>
<p>
    <strong>Consent</strong> (Art. 6.1.a GDPR) would be used only, where applicable, for sending
    non-essential communications (for example, newsletters about our activity), which you could
    accept separately and withdraw at any time.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Mandatory nature of the data.</strong> The data requested at each stage are necessary
    for the stated purposes. Refusal to provide them will result in our being unable to process
    your application, formalise your membership or manage the collection of the fee, as the case
    may be.
</p>

<h2>For how long do we keep your data?</h2>
<ul>
    <li>We keep your data <strong>for as long as the membership relationship continues</strong> and you do not request cancellation.</li>
    <li>
        Following cancellation, the data are <strong>blocked</strong> (kept available solely for
        the competent authorities) for the legal limitation periods applicable to liabilities:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>4 years</strong>, for tax obligations arising from the limitation period for tax (Arts. 66 to 68 of Ley 58/2003, General Tributaria).</li>
            <li><strong>6 years</strong>, for the obligation to retain accounting documentation (Art. 30 of the Código de Comercio).</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>The <strong>SEPA direct debit mandate</strong> is kept for the period laid down by the applicable SEPA rules for direct debits.</li>
</ul>
<p>Once those periods have elapsed, the data are <strong>securely deleted</strong>.</p>

<h2>To which recipients is your data disclosed?</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>The bank:</strong> for carrying out the direct debit and collecting the fee (SEPA direct debit).</li>
    <li><strong>Data processors:</strong> providers supplying services necessary for the operation of the site and the management of membership (for example, web hosting and email), which process the data solely on behalf of the Association and in accordance with its instructions, under a processing agreement pursuant to Art. 28 GDPR.</li>
    <li><strong>No other disclosures</strong> are made to third parties, except where legally required (for example, to the Tax Authorities or to courts and tribunals where the applicable legislation so requires).</li>
    <li><strong>No international data transfers are made.</strong></li>
</ul>

<h2>What are your rights when you provide us with your data?</h2>
<p>You may exercise the following rights:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Access:</strong> to find out what data of yours we are processing.</li>
    <li><strong>Rectification:</strong> to correct inaccurate or incomplete data.</li>
    <li><strong>Erasure:</strong> to request the deletion of your data when it is no longer necessary.</li>
    <li><strong>Objection:</strong> to object to certain processing.</li>
    <li><strong>Restriction:</strong> to request that processing be restricted in the cases provided for.</li>
    <li><strong>Portability:</strong> to receive your data in a structured, commonly used format, or to have it transmitted to another controller.</li>
    <li><strong>Withdrawal of consent</strong> given, where applicable, for non-essential communications, without this affecting the lawfulness of the processing carried out beforehand.</li>
</ul>
<p>
    <strong>How to exercise them?</strong> You may exercise your rights by writing to
    [CONTACT EMAIL] or to the address [REGISTERED ADDRESS], stating the right you wish to exercise
    and enclosing a copy of a document proving your identity.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Complaint to the supervisory authority.</strong> If you consider that the processing
    of your data does not comply with the legislation, you may lodge a complaint with the Spanish
    Data Protection Agency (AEPD), located at C/ Jorge Juan, 6, 28001 Madrid, or through its
    electronic office at <a href="https://www.aepd.es" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.aepd.es</a>.
</p>

